the maid * Harry Davenport as Grandpa * Henry H. Daniels Jr. as Alonzo " Lon " Smith Jr. * Joan Carroll as Agnes Smith * June Lockhart as Lucille Ballard * Robert Sully as Warren Sheffield * Hugh Marlowe as Colonel Darly * Chill Wills as Mr. Neely the iceman MUSIC Section::::Music .
The musical score for the film was adapted by Roger Edens , who also served as an uncredited associate producer .
Georgie Stoll conducted the orchestrations of Conrad Salinger .
Some of the songs in the film are from around the time of the St Louis Exposition .
Others were written for the movie .
